![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/78eb36f8-a319-449f-b3f9-49897b456ca8/20250221_172257.jpg)

JIMMY USO DEF. DREW MCINTYRE

Jimmy Uso rolls up Drew McIntyre off of a Reversed Alabama Slam attempt. Post match, Drew McIntyre attacks Jimmy Uso and threatens to big boot his head into the steel ring post. Security stops him. McIntyre acts like he's leaving then runs back and give Jimmy a claymore.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/0c3fa9e3-bdc8-41e4-bb38-98ef55e107e4/Screenshot_20250221_172510.jpg)

Jacob Fatu and Tama Tonga confront Jacob Fatu about Tama getting taken out last week.

Solo says it was an accident. Jacob says he knows because if it wasn't, Solo wouldn't be standing up right now.

Solo says this is exactly why he loves Jacob. Jacob doesn't seem convinced. Solo says he wants to be in their corner against Priest and Strowman tonight. Jacob says Solo is gonna have to pull his weight after being gone and he's in the match instead of Tama.

